  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">African Activists for Climate Justice - FM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to amplify and unite the voices in Africa to ensure that women, youth and local and indigenous communities defend and realize their human rights and live a decent and dignified life in a healthy and sustainable environment, within the context of the climate emergency. 
The Project&#x2019;s long-term impact is a strong and inclusive African movement that has mobilised citizens, companies and governments (local, national, regional, global) in support of climate justice.

PACJA in collaboration with four other partners,  Oxfam Novib, Natural Justice, African Women Communications Network (FEMNET) and African Youth Commission (AYC), as a consortium,  believe that all people have the right to live a decent and dignified life in a healthy environment. 

FEMNET in Mozambique will lead in strengthening climate resilience and Justice for rural communities with key climate actors working with marginalized groups and local communities, particularly women and youth, who are at the frontline of the climate crisis, are strengthened to claim their rights for climate justice and climate resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
